A very clever page, and a clever idea.  The fundamental flaw that I
see is that anyone sniffing the line to pick up credit card numbers
would also be picking up the text for the page, would see the
javascript, and could therefore quickly figure out the card number. 
So the cryptographic protection you are offering is very weak.  It
does provide the security that it would not be a method an attacker
was looking for.  This is known in the trade as "security through
obscurity". 

Nevertheless, it's a good idea that could be developed and 
strengthened in several ways -- using java would be much more 
powerful, too.  Depending on how it works out, it could be a *very* 
good idea.

